 Sub-Saharan Africa, West Africa, and the Sahel from 
 1960 to 1995, calculated from USDA data. The continent, area and smaller area show somewhat different 
 year-to-year difference/different version, but a almost the same 20-yr 
 period of yield spoiling from 1964 until their lowest 
 point in 1984. Most (in a surprising and interesting way), after 1984, there is a 
 sustained improvement in yields through 1995 in all 
 three areas. 
 Total production, shown in index-number terms on 
 Fig. 3, is a result of both produces and area. Again, 
 USDA data show a break after 1984, which is most 
 dramatic for the Sahel. All three areas had significant 
 increases in total cereal grain production from 1960 to 
 1984, but growth speeded up sharply in the following 
 ten years especially in the Sahel. 
